<div id="content_1718" class="comment" name="comment_1718">
  <img class="avatar" src="/people/photo_bits/87.jpg" alt="Louis Rosenfeld's avatar" />
  <h4><a href="/person/87-louisrosenfeld" id="author">Louis Rosenfeld</a></h4>
  <p id="reputation_points">7 Reputation points</p>
  <p>Posted <strong>2003/09/24 @ 22:17PM</strong> with <span id="content_1718_points"> </span></p>

 <div class="cmt"> <p>Cliff, interesting comment.  I wonder if decreasing reliance is due to better IA on sites in general, as you&#8217;re suggesting, or to users being more familiar with the architecture of the specific site you&#8217;re testing?  Probably a bit of both, but I&#8217;m wondering if your data comes from testing usage of multiple sites or just one?</p></div>

  
  
</div>
<script type="text/javascript">
//<![CDATA[
